.TH STRETTO 1 "2026-07-09" "stretto" "User Commands"
.\" Hand-written; no version in .TH (stretto --version is authoritative).
.\" Bump the date above whenever this page changes. The help<->man
.\" drift gate in tests/test_cli.sh asserts every --help flag appears
.\" here.
.SH NAME
stretto \- tiny deterministic generative music synthesizer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B stretto
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B stretto
.B \-\-render
.I seconds
.RI ( out.wav | \- )
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B stretto
.B \-\-midi\-list\-devices
.br
.B stretto
.RB { \-h | \-\-help | \-\-version }
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B stretto
is a generative ambient music synthesizer in C99: no malloc, a single
static 128 KB arena, and a packed binary measured in tens of kilobytes.
Run bare, it plays live out the default audio device (PulseAudio on
Linux, waveOut on Windows) and draws an ASCII oscilloscope sized to the
terminal. With
.BR \-\-render ,
it writes a stereo 16\-bit 48 kHz WAV instead \(em or streams it to
stdout for pipelines.
.PP
Eleven voice slots (super\-saw bass, section\-morphing chord pads,
Karplus\-Strong/FM melody, three drums) are driven by cellular
automata, Markov chains, an L\-system phrase generator, Euclidean
rhythms, a 96\-bar song\-section state machine, and long\-term motif
memory, through a Schroeder reverb, stereo delay, soft saturation, and
a brickwall\-limited compressor.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS General
.TP
.BI \-\-seed " N"
Fix all generative state to the unsigned integer
.IR N .
Identical seed and flags produce byte\-identical audio on every
supported platform (see
.BR DETERMINISM ).
Without it, the seed derives from the clock and is reported by the
resume line so the run stays recallable.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-ui
Headless live mode: no terminal raw mode, no oscilloscope, no key
handler. For scripts and CI.
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage to stdout and exit 0, ignoring all other arguments.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print
.RB \(dq "stretto <version>" \(dq
and the license block to stdout and exit 0. The version is embedded at
build time from
.BR "git describe" .
.SS Render mode
.TP
.BI \-\-render " seconds" " " ( out.wav | \- )
Render
.I seconds
(1..3600) of audio to a WAV file. The output argument
.B \-
streams the WAV to stdout, byte\-identical to the file output \(em the
RIFF header is written up front, so pipes need no seeking. A file
literally named
.B \-
needs
.BR ./\- .
A downstream that closes early ends the render via SIGPIPE.
.SS MIDI input
.TP
.BR \-\-midi " [" N ]
Open MIDI input device
.I N
(0\-based, from
.BR \-\-midi\-list\-devices ),
or subscribe to every readable input port if
.I N
is omitted. Exits 1 if no device is available. Never opened in render
mode. Notes map through the active scale; velocity 0 is note\-off.
.TP
.B \-\-midi\-default
Alias for
.BR "\-\-midi 0" .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-midi
Explicit MIDI opt\-out; identical to omitting all MIDI flags.
.TP
.B \-\-midi\-list\-devices
Print one line per MIDI input device as
.RI \(dq "index name" \(dq
and exit 0.
.TP
.BI \-\-midi\-channel " N"
Accept only MIDI channel
.I N
(1..16). Requires
.B \-\-midi
or
.BR \-\-midi\-default ;
omit the flag to accept all channels.
.SS Initial state (preset capture)
Each flag sets one live\-tunable parameter before the first sample.
Ranges mirror the live\-key clamps exactly; out\-of\-range values are
hard errors, never silent clamps. Output is a pure function of
.RB ( \-\-seed ,
flags).
.TP
.BI \-\-scale " name" | 0\-5
dorian, lydian, phrygian, locrian, harmminor, mixolydian.
.TP
.BI \-\-bar\-ms " 760\-7600"
Bar length in milliseconds (default 2000).
.TP
.BI \-\-gate " 32\-255"
Melody gate probability.
.TP
.BI \-\-mod\-depth " 100\-8000"
FM modulation depth.
.TP
.BI \-\-cutoff " 30\-180"
Filter cutoff base. The untouched default (200) sits above this dial
range; omit the flag to keep it.
.TP
.BI \-\-resonance " 0\-180"
Filter resonance base.
.TP
.BI \-\-lfo\-depth " 0\-255"
Filter LFO depth.
.TP
.BI \-\-filter\-mode " name" | 0\-3
lp, hp, bp, notch.
.TP
.BI \-\-reverb " 0\-256"
Reverb wet mix.
.TP
.BI \-\-delay " 0\-256"
Delay wet mix.
.TP
.BI \-\-feedback " 0\-200"
Delay feedback.
.TP
.BI \-\-comp\-threshold " 8000\-30000"
Compressor threshold.
.SH LIVE-MODE KEYS
.TS
l l.
SPACE	force a mutation now
+ / \-	tempo faster / slower (10%)
[ / ]	FM mod depth down / up
s	cycle scale
g / G	gate probability down / up
r / R	reverb wet down / up
d / D	delay wet down / up
f / F	delay feedback down / up
c / C	filter cutoff down / up
n / N	filter resonance down / up
m / M	filter LFO depth down / up
t	cycle filter mode (LP/HP/BP/notch)
l / L	compressor threshold down / up
?	toggle help overlay
q	quit (prints the resume line)
.TE
.PP
Ctrl\-C, SIGTERM, SIGQUIT, and SIGHUP restore the terminal and print
the resume line before the process dies by the signal.
.SH RESUME LINE
On quit, live mode prints one pasteable line to stderr:
.PP
.EX
resume with: --seed 3735928559 --scale lydian --bar-ms 1500
.EE
.PP
It contains the run's seed (also captured for clock\-seeded runs) plus
only the parameters you explicitly set via flag or key \(em the
synth's internal mutation drift is never printed, because the seed
alone reproduces that drift from bar 0. Recall reproduces a run with
those values
.B from bar 0
(keystroke timing is not replayed; a mid\-session scale change alters
the chord\-progression path from that point). MIDI CC tweaks are not
captured. Render mode prints a seed\-only line at render start.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; 1 on usage or runtime errors (unknown flags,
out\-of\-range values, unopenable output, unavailable MIDI device).
Termination by SIGINT, SIGPIPE, or SIGTERM is reported by the shell as
130, 141, or 143 respectively.
.SH EXAMPLES
Play live with a fixed seed and a brighter, faster start:
.PP
.EX
stretto --seed 42 --cutoff 160 --bar-ms 1500
.EE
.PP
Render one minute to a file, reproducibly:
.PP
.EX
stretto --render 60 song.wav --seed 12345
.EE
.PP
Stream a render through ffmpeg without touching disk:
.PP
.EX
stretto --render 60 - --seed 7 | ffmpeg -i - out.flac
.EE
.PP
Recall a session captured by the resume line:
.PP
.EX
stretto --seed 3735928559 --scale lydian --bar-ms 1500
.EE
.SH DETERMINISM
With
.B \-\-seed
.IR N ,
audio output is byte\-identical across runs and across the supported
build targets (Linux glibc, Windows). The runtime engine is
integer\-only; the seed plus the initial\-state flags are the complete
input contract. A bit\-exact SHA\-256 regression gates every change.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs: https://github.com/quanticsoul4772/stretto/issues
